CLASS IX AND X
ENGLISH COMPOSITIONS
LESSON – 4
AMPLIFICATION
SOLUTIONS
EXERCISES
Amplify or expand the followings:
1. The person I like most
We meet many people in our lives, but there are some people who have great impact
on our lives. I like my mother a lot. She is an ideal lady. She is very polite, affectionate and
intelligent. She also manages the family very nicely. She does every piece of household
works. Moreover, she takes great care of all of us. She is ready to sacrifice her own happiness
for her family. She is a woman of delicate taste. She bears a good moral character. She
advises us to follow, the path of truth and honesty. She is very important to me. She is my
good role model, and I love her for many more reasons. She is truly an inspiration for me. I
must learn from her. She is entirely best. A mother’s love is unlike any other and our one-of-
a-kind relationship can never be compared.
2. Being a teenager
Being a teenager is really tough period of Man’s life. It’s the stage where you have to
deal and cope with the most changes, in your whole life. This transition from childhood to
adulthood is smooth for some, but rough for others. The most important thing about being a
teenager is responsibility. When you’re a teenager, you get blamed for anything wrong that
you do, get grounded, punished, unlike before when you were a child. This is a crucial age
through which everyone passes.
Page | 2
3. Meeting an old friend
Everyone has one best friend. The one friend that remains constant in your life, no
matter how far apart you live. Sometimes for some reason you are not able to see an old friend
and suddenly you meet your friend after a long time. Your joy knows no bounds. It is as if you
come upon a lost treasure. Both of you narrate the stories of success and failure. The time
stopped for both of you, you are unmindful of time and continue reminding each other the
golden past of friendship. It looks like your friendship has been cemented once more. You
seem to be the happiest and luckiest person in the world.
4. Need for vocational education
Vocational Education is a system or course of study which prepares individuals for
jobs that are based on manual or practical activities. Vocational education is a multifaceted
one as it tends to focus around several careers which include auto repair, wood working,
carpentry, blacksmith, cosmetology, and other fields. It makes an individual responsible and
independent whereas those who study regular courses lack in this sphere. This type of
education is a great asset to the economy. Our government need not import foreign
technicians on higher wages as our own can do the required work. School drop-outs and
adults can also receive this type of education as it provides an opportunity to learn a skill or
trade. This education provides stable jobs as these are the jobs whose demand is never
fulfilled.
Page | 3
5. Regionalism in India
Regionalism is a political ideology that focuses on the national or normative interests
of a particular region, group of regions or other subnational entity. These may be delineated
by political divisions, cultural boundaries, linguistic regions, and religious geography, among
others. India is a country of unity in diversity, where the power of unity is strong in spite of
diversities in area, population and human-cultural factors. This power helped to develop
‘Indian Federation’. The rise of regionalism in India is due to diversity and variation in the
Indian economic and social culture.
6. Man, the destroyer of environment
Every living and non-living beings is related to environment. Environment plays a
major role in human beings. It provides us with fresh air that we breathe, water that we drinks,
food and almost all the resources for our survival. Yet, we human beings are overusing the
resources and exploiting the environment with the activities that harm it. Human activities
transform the natural environment into human environment by constructing buildings,
industries, firms, cutting woods, and using landscapes for the purpose of development. It is
vital to use the natural resources carefully and avoid harming the environment for the healthy
and naturally wealthy life.
7. Industry is the mother of good luck
Great men were all industrious in their own spheres. They had labored for a long time
before attaining success but very few fortunate men inherit ancestral fortune without proper
industry. But they too must be industrious to enjoy their fortune properly; otherwise they will
waste it within a short time. They will soon become poor and lead a miserable life. A student
can shine well in life if he is industrious. A nation prospers if the people are industrious. So
we all should give up idleness and work hard if we wish to have good luck in life. A man who
has been in adversity can feel for others in distress. But a person who has always been in
prosperity cannot feel for people in adversity, because he has never known how painful it is to
suffer hardships.
Page | 4
8. The crown and glory of life is character
It is rightly said that the crown and glory of life is character. Character plays a pivotal
role in the life of human beings. It is as significant for a man as a crown for a king. It is the
glory of a man’s life. Character reflects the trait and personality of a man. A man is judged by
his character. A person who has good character is respected and honoured in society. One
rises in life in proportion to the strength of one’s character. Character gives self-satisfaction to
a person. He can lead a happy and contended life. It is only character that distinguishes man
from beast. So, each and every human being should endeavour to develop a great character.
9. We live in deeds, not in year
or
One crowded hour of glorious life is worth an age without a name
It means a long life is not necessary to live long but a short life can also make a
person’s life long. The good work we do makes us remembered for many years even after our
death. The value of living depends on the amount of good work one has done and without
doing any good work life has no value . Every human being should try to live a life of value
and worth in terms of betterment of God’s creation. So, short life spent in the service of
humanity is better than a long life spent in a self-centered sequestered corner.
10. An idle brain is the devil’s workshop
Evil thoughts enter our brain easily when we remain idle. When a man has nothing to
do, all sorts of evil ideas come to his mind. This will turn the man into Devil. When a person
has nothing to do, he naturally becomes lazy because of his idleness. This is when he starts
thinking of evil things. But when a person is occupied with work, he does not have time to
dwell on anything but his own work. So, we should never be idle but stay occupied with work
and keep ourselves busy.
Page | 5
11. Goodness is better than greatness
Goodness is one of the cardinal virtues without which one is not fully entitled to call
himself a man. Greatness is normally measured in terms of rank, position, wealth and
influence. On such contrast goodness is superior to greatness for several reasons. It is open to
all men to be good, but all cannot be great. One is within the reach of human efforts, the other
has besides human endeavour, an element of luck or chance. Sometimes, greatness is inherited
in the shape of position and wealth, yet goodness is either inborn or cultivated through
diligence. It is not necessary that the son of a good man may also be good, whereas the rich
father leaves enough property for the next generation to roll in wealth. Goodness has, on the
other hand, greater inclination and scope for serving humanity than greatness. It is truly said,
“a good name outlines great riches and rank”. For these and other reasons, goodness is spoken
of as greater than greatness. The want of all times is the want of good men.
12. Houses are built to live in and not to look on
It is criticism of how often people worry too much about buying and using things they
really don’t need. It suggests that people need to focus on what they need first and only then
they can start thinking about luxurious and glamour things. So, we need to focus on our aim
and target to reach our goal, besides unwanted circumstances of life.
13. Great talkers are never great doers
In this statement “talkers” refers to those persons who usually talk too much and
“doers” are those people who get actively involved in something, rather than just thinking or
talking about it. There are people in this world who only love to talk but stay away from being
actively involved in work. In other words they are bad workers. On the other hand there are
also people who are known as great doers. Doers are not fond of talking, they usually remain
reticent about their activities and engage themselves whole-heartedly in work. The statement
“great talkers are never great doers” distinguishes between these two categories of people.
Talkers and doers are really temperamentally different. It is often said that doing is more
difficult than saying. So, doers should be more appreciated than sayers.
Page | 6
14. Train up a child in the way he should go
The proverb refers to training a child to develop good habits, make appropriate
decisions, and to follow God so they continue to do well in adulthood. Discipline is an
integral part of raising as a godly child. When we discipline our children, they receive
wisdom, and they will bring in peace and respect. In fact even at a tender age children are able
to discern that discipline is rooted in love. That is why children who grow up in homes
without discipline often feel unloved and are more likely to disobey authority as they grow
older. Parents have been given the privilege of being stewards of their children’s life for a
very short time, but the teaching and training they provide is eternal.
15. The Noblest man that live on earth,
Are Men whose hands are brown with toil
There are people who are considered as noble but they are very devilish, hardwork
depends on your capability and fitness. If someone has a back to back problem and cannot
work hard but completes given task on time accurately, then we cannot question a person’s
sincerity towards work. This may be true that hardwork, means dedication but in this century
smart-work. It is not necessary to physically torture yourself to express your commitment, but
being noble means to be kind and free from all negatives.
16. Perseverance is the very hinge of all virtue
Perseverance means constant effort to achieve something. It is the best of all human
virtues because it is the key to success. We can succeed in life without perseverance,
steadfastness and determination. Perseverance implies a discipline of mind and body, constant
effort, self-restraint and self- sacrifice. Human life in earth is full of hardships and
misfortunes. As soon as we overcome one hardship, a new one appears. If we have
perseverance, we can overcome any number of difficulties and attain success. But when we
lose heart at the sight of obstacles, we cannot succeed. We shouldn’t grumble when a new
difficulty arises. We should rather accept the challenge. If we have perseverance, we can take
the risk of solving the difficulties. So it is said that perseverance is the key to success.
Page | 7
17. The real dignity of a man lies not in what he has but in what he is
A man’s real achievement is in his dignity. Dignity is not an inborn quality of human
beings. We cannot measure a man by status, possession or economic development. Man does
not get the dignity from his forefathers. His personality determines his dignity. We know that
virtuous men are always honoured. Some people feel pride in their wealth. They think that
wealth will increase their dignity. But it is not true. The real dignity of a man depends on
personal quality which upholds a man’s image. A rich man gets importance in society for his
wealth. But it is very temporary. But an honest man who has dignity will influence people a
lot. People will respect him in his lifetime. So we can say that a man’s dignity depends on his
personal quality and does not rely on property.
18. Life indeed would be dull, if there were no difficulty
One never attains the sense of happiness unless he has tasted the pangs of trouble and
difficulties. Life devoid of difficulties is food without spice. Only difficulties make you rock,
strong from outwardly as well as inwardly. Sorrow and hardship is nothing but the friends
which will make you strong, confident and successful. You will merely remain an amateur in
the spheres of life if you try to avoid difficulties in your life. So, we need to learn how to face
the difficulties of life. Make difficulties your tool to churn strength to fight with the ordeals of
life and become the ultimate winners.
19. Tell me not in mournful members,
Life is but an empty dream
Life is beautiful but not always easy, it has problems, too, and the challenge lies in facing
them with courage. We should never complain about our whims and failure , instead we
should try to achieve in an optimistic way. The pessimistic man always think that nothing can
be achieved and he remains disappointed with sorrow and mourn of this life. So, we should
not feel sad, and avoid pessimistic thoughts, even when we are in sorrowful moments, but try
to overcome the problem in a positive way.
Page | 8
20. Full many a flowers is born to blush unseen,
And waste its sweatness on the desert air
There are lots of people who are born beautiful and talented or gifted in some way, but
they are born into situations where their beauty, talent or gift has no way to manifest itself and
is utterly wasted. We should not harm our beautiful life, and being a man we should do some
valuable work for mankind.
21. Only the actions of the just,
Smell sweet and blossom in their dust
No men can live forever in this temporary world. But a man with his good and kind
works can make this short span of life meaningful and worth mentioning. Great persons,
philosophers and good people have attained the status of immortality through their
contributions for the benefit and welfare of mankind. One should remember that good deeds
only live after us. Everyone should try to do something useful for mankind, so that we may be
remembered even when we have left this world.
